Newcastle host Sunderland in the Tyne-Wear derby on Sunday . 
  John Carver was assistant to Ruud Gullit in 1999 when he controversially left out Alan Shearer and Duncan Ferguson . 
  Newcastle lost 2-1 to Sunderland at St James' Park in the 1999 derby . 
  Carver is in charge of his hometown club for the first time . 
  He was also assistant to Alan Pardew when he was at the club . 
 